CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1776801953
OL,3,CMental health staff to strike over pay
OL,4,Cdisputes
OL,6,FMental health staff are set to strike
OL,7,Fover pay, UNISON has confirmed.
OL,9,FDrivers at Greater Manchester Mental
OL,10,FHealth Trust will begin three further
OL,11,Fweeks of strikes after bosses ignored
OL,12,Ftheir own report and failed to improve
OL,13,Fstaff pay, the union reports.
OL,15,FThe drivers - who transport samples,
OL,16,Fmedication, linen and food across
OL,17,FGreater Manchester ` say they have
OL,18,Falready completed a job evaluation
OL,19,Fthat found their roles should be
OL,20,Fupgraded to a higher pay grade.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1776801953
OL,3,CMental health staff to strike over pay
OL,4,Cdisputes
OL,6,FBut the union says bosses have not
OL,7,Facted on the findings and have instead
OL,8,Fasked for a second opinion from
OL,9,Fanother NHS trust. It says 11 drivers
OL,10,Fhave been left thousands of pounds out
OL,11,Fof pocket.
OL,13,FUNISON North West regional organiser
OL,14,FPaddy Cleary said: "Trust bosses have
OL,15,Ffailed to act in time and workers have
OL,16,Fbeen left with no choice but to
OL,17,Fstrike. Nobody wants to take this
OL,18,Fstep, but staff are underpaid for the
OL,19,Fvital work they do ` as the trust's
OL,20,Fown report makes clear.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1776801953
OL,3,CMental health staff to strike over pay
OL,4,Cdisputes
OL,6,F"The job evaluation process was
OL,7,Ffollowed correctly. These staff should
OL,8,Fbe on a higher rate of pay. Instead of
OL,9,Fputting this right, senior managers
OL,10,Fhave chosen to delay the inevitable by
OL,11,Fseeking unnecessary advice.
OL,13,F"The trust should implement the report
OL,14,Ffindings as a matter of urgency and
OL,15,Fpay workers what they're due."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
